cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new approach for dynamic motion planning for legged robots. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper formulates a trajectory optimization problem based on a compact form of the robot dynamics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper uses direct transcription to numerically solve the optimization. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents results on a hydraulic quadruped robot (HyQ) which may involve some computer vision techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also less likely but possible as the paper presents a new approach for solving the optimal control problem of a floating base constrained multibody system.
